# Streamlit App Walkthrough (Finger Mode)

## Summary
The app now assigns specific notes to each finger, turning your hands into the instrument.

## Mappings
| Hand | Finger | Natural (Straight) | Sharp (Curled) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Left** | Pinky | C3 | C#3 |
| **Left** | Ring | D3 | D#3 |
| **Left** | Middle | E3 | F3 |
| **Left** | Index | F3 | F#3 |
| **Left** | Thumb | G3 | G#3 |
| **Right** | Thumb | A3 | A#3 |
| **Right** | Index | B3 | C4 |
| **Right** | Middle | C4 | C#4 |
| **Right** | Ring | D4 | D#4 |
| **Right** | Pinky | E4 | F4 |

## How to Play
1. **Strike Down**: Move a finger down fast to play its note.
2. **Curl**: Bend your finger while striking to play the **Sharp (#)** version.
3. **Chords**: Strike with multiple fingers at once!

## How to Run
```bash
./.venv/bin/streamlit run app.py
```
Open the URL shown in the terminal (usually http://localhost:8501).
